I will never be able to find the words for how grateful I am for Ohio State Volleyball. This program has challenged and allowed me to grow both as a volleyball player and a person. These experiences and opportunities are something I will forever be thankful for. Closing a chapter in life is never easy but I am so proud of these girls and everything we have accomplished. 

To my family, thank you for the endless love & support over all these crazy years. Without it, I would not be who I am today and i am forever grateful for all the sacrifices you all have made for me. 

To my teammates, thank you for always loving & supporting me. Each and everyone one of you have made an impact not only on my career, but most importantly my life. Sisters forever. I love you all. 

To my coaches & other administrators, thank you for giving me this once in a life time opportunity. Little me would be so proud but without you guys this wouldn’t have been possible.

& to all the other people involved, seriously thank you for being apart of this journey with me and allowing me to play the sport I love so much.
i am super excited to see what is next!!! :) 

Thank you Buckeye Nation. It’s been fun! 
Forever a Buckeye❤️

As I drove away from Columbus for the final time, I was filled with so many emotions. Sad, excited, scared… but I couldn’t stop the tears when I was thinking about ALL of the people who have made a positive impact on my life during my 4 years here at Ohio State. When first moving here everyone raved bout how Columbus has the best sports, food, entertainment, etc.. but no one told me how amazing the people would be. Thank you to everyone who has loved and supported me along my journey. I could not imagine my life without you. I have grown into someone who I am proud of & I could not have done that without this place. Columbus is forever my home & I will miss everything about it dearly. This place hold so many memories that I will cherish forever and having to leave was so bittersweet. 
To all my people, I love you. This is not a goodbye. And to the people I may never cross paths with again, thank you. Thank you for making this the best 4 years of my life. So much love for the 614 & all these incredible people (& so many more not featured) ❤️❤️❤️
